Package: autoimage
Type: Package
Title: Multiple Heat Maps for Projected Coordinates
Version: 2.2.2
Date: 2020-12-21
Author: Joshua French
Maintainer: Joshua French <joshua.french@ucdenver.edu>
BugReports: https://github.com/jfrench/autoimage/issues
Description: Functions for displaying multiple images  or scatterplots with a color 
    scale, i.e., heat maps, possibly with projected coordinates.  The
    package relies on the base graphics system, so graphics are
    rendered rapidly.
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
Imports:
    colorspace,
    fields,
    mapproj,
    ggplot2,
    maps,
    MBA
Suggests:
    abind,
    testthat,
    spatstat,
    gear,
    broom,
    gridExtra,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
License: GPL (>=2)
LazyData: TRUE
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
